description:
ABC News - Made in America

Overview
-World News' new series looking at how we can bring jobs back to the U.S. 
-Tech giant Apple brings back production of one of its lines of computers to United States. 
-The average gift-giver will spend about $738; last year $2.5 billion went toward gifts made in China. 
-Made in America team investigates just who is making our stars and stripes. 
-World's largest retailer plans investment in US-made goods over the next 10 years. 
-John Ratzenberger explains the shortage of skilled workers in America.
-U.S. exports increase; signs of economy on the rise. 
-U.S. shoe companies express interest in keeping sneaker manufacturing here at home. 
David Muir looks at how holiday spending can translate into American jobs. 
-Mom entrepreneur reaps reward with idea that could also help grow jobs. 
-US manufacturing, despite a contraction in its workforce, can still take on China because of increasing productivity
-2014 omnibus appropriations bill provision calls for the nation's military to purchase flags made in the country.
